631\u064e\u0629\u064e \u0623\u064e\u0646\u064e\u0651\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\u0627\u0646&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\u0627\u0646","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/faith-iman\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":19195,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2014\/05\/19\/sahabah-recite-surah-al-asr\/","url_meta":{"origin":32220,"position":4},"title":"Hadith on Quran: Companions recite Surat al-&#8216;Asr before parting","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"May 19, 2014","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Madinah reported: Whenever two men among the companions of the Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, would meet, they would not part until one of them recited to the other, \u201cBy the time, surely mankind is in loss,\u201d (103:1) and the other would bid\u00a0him farewell with peace. Source:\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Quran Exegesis \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0641\u0633\u064a\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Quran Exegesis \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0641\u0633\u064a\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/quran-exegesis-tafsir\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":15449,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2013\/07\/28\/salaam-coming-going\/","url_meta":{"origin":32220,"position":5},"title":"Hadith on Salaam: Greet with peace when coming and going","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"July 28, 2013","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Huraira reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cWhen one of you arrives in a gathering, let him greet them with peace. When he intends to leave, let him leave them with peace. The first greeting is not more worthy than the last.\u201d Source:\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_